<p><a href="#sdfootnote41anc" name="sdfootnote41sym">41</a> Vito Acconci, <em>Notes on My Photography 1969-70</em>, w: <em>Vito Acconci: Photographic Work</em>, Brooke Alexander, New York 1988 (przedruk w: Douglas Fogle, <em>The Last Picture Show. Artists Using Photography, 1960-1982</em>, Walker Art Center, Minneapolis 2003, s. 184).</p>
<p><a href="#sdfootnote42anc" name="sdfootnote42sym">42</a> Maurice Merleau-Ponty, <em>Fenomenologia percepcji</em>, przeł. M. Kowalska, J. Migasiński, Aletheia, Warszawa 2001, s. 8. Christine Poggi pisze więcej na temat fenomenologicznego wymiaru prac Acconciego. Zob. eadem, <em>Following Acconci/Targeting Vision</em>, w:<em> Performing the Body/Performing the Text,</em> red. A. Jones, A. Stevenson, Routledge, London 1999, s. 255-272.</p>
